<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-510-247  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 510 247.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 25 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Dariana ships Sleuth programs for Windows, Mac. (DarianaTechnology Group's System Sleuth diagnostic software ) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Dariana Technology Group Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   System Sleuth (Performance analysis software) (productintroduction)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (computerprograms).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware MigrationUtility ProgramsSystems software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>DARIANA SHIPS SLEUTH PROGRAMS FOR WINDOWS, MAC BUENA PARK, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A., 1990 SEP 25 (NB) -- Dariana Technology Group, makers of the SystemSleuth program for IBM PCs, shipped Windows Sleuth and MacSleuth, whichprovide the same kind of diagnostic power to users of the Microsoft Windows3.0 operating environment and the Apple Macintosh.andM;The Windows version features 11 modules which help users set up newcomputers, reconfigure systems to operate under Windows 3.0, troubleshootnetworks, learn the secrets of programs, cross- examine memory and harddisks, figure out problems with displays and otherwise examine the hardwareand software, without opening the computer.andM;The Macintosh version offers 13 modules to set up new Macs, reconfigureexisting systems, troubleshoot AppleTalk networks, learn about devices underthe control of the Chooser Desk Accessory, and dig for interrupt queues andresources, again wtihout opening the computer.andM;Both programs retail for $149 and are distributed by Ingram Micro D andMerisel, and sold by retail chains including Egghead and Software City.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900921/Press Contact: Frank Westall, Dariana TechnologyGroup, 714-994-7400)</TEXT></DOC>